UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 349
1 AN ACT relating to postnuptial agreements.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 403 IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 A postnuptial agreement shall be void and unenforceable unless:
6 (1) It contains:
7 (a) The date on which the document was initially received by each party or his
8 or her independent legal counsel, acknowledged before a notary public by
9 both parties to the agreement; and
10 (b) Conspicuous statements of the following:
11 1. That the drafter of the document does not represent both parties to the
12 agreement;
13 2. That each party is advised to retain independent legal counsel;
14 3. That each party shall be afforded the opportunity to conduct an
15 independent assessment of financial information and valuation of
16 assets of the parties; and
17 4. That in the event of fraud, the agreement may be declared null and
18 void;
19 (2) It is executed by the parties to the agreement in the presence of each other before
20 a notary public and two (2) witnesses;
21 (3) It includes the signatures of the legal counsel of each party to the agreement if
22 counsel has been retained; and
23 (4) Sixty (60) days have elapsed between the date of initial receipt of the document
24 under subsection (1) of this section and the date of its execution under subsection
25 (2) of this section.
